China Resources (836)  Power Holdings Co. a
power generation company, and  China Resources Gas Group Ltd. (1193) , a
natural gas distributor, are negotiating a possible merger to
form an integrated energy group under their state-owned parent
China Resources (Holdings) Co.  Shares of both companies have been suspended pending an
announcement, the two companies said in separate statements to
the Hong Kong Stock Exchange today. Neither provided details of
their discussion nor a time line for the negotiations.  China Resources Powerâ€™s market valuation is HK$121.2
billion ($15.6 billion), while China Resources Gas has a market
